<blockquote style="BORDER-LEFT:#ccc 1px solid;MARGIN:0px 0px 0px 0.8ex;PADDING-LEFT:1ex" class="gmail_quote">Hi Ghobad,<br><br>The error message means the OpenMPI wants to use cl.exe - the compiler<br>from Microsoft Visual Studio.<br>
<br>Here <a href="http://www.open-mpi.org/software/ompi/v1.5/ms-windows.php" target="_blank">http://www.open-mpi.org/software/ompi/v1.5/ms-windows.php</a> is it stated:<br><br>This is the first binary release for Windows, with basic MPI libraries<br>
and executables. The supported platforms are Windows XP, Windows<br>Vista, Windows Server 2003/2008, and Windows 7 (including both 32 and<br>64 bit versions). The installers were configured with CMake 2.8.1 and<br>compiled under Visual Studio 2010, and they support for C/C++<br>
compilers of Visual Studio 2005, 2008 and 2010.<br><br>So, to compile MPI programs you probably need one of this compilers to<br>be installed.<br><br>Best regards.<br>- Dima.<br><br>2012/5/10 Ghobad Zarrinchian &lt;<a href="mailto:gzarrin.edu@gmail.com">gzarrin.edu@gmail.com</a>&gt;:<br>

